Whether you've got the knowledge  tools  time or space to do the things you've always wanted to do  everything is "figureoutable."   I became "Anne of All Trades" out of necessity. With no background in farming or making things  I wanted to learn to raise my own food  fix things when they break and build the things I need.   12 years ago I got my first pet  planted my first seed and picked up my first tool.   My goal is to learn and share traditional techniques and skills while showing my peers how to get from where they are to where they want to go  how to do the things they are passionate about  and what can be done TODAY to engage their own community and grow deep roots.   Whether it's carving spoons  making my own hand tools  restoring my antique truck or growing heirloom tomatoes  the farm and workshop definitely keep me busy and support - whether financially through Patreon  through shopping my affiliate links  through buying merchandise  plans or project videos  or even just liking  commenting  and sharing my content with others helps me GREATLY to keep producing quality content to share.
